><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwoonx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#333333>(9/15/02 3:18:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epic Pet?</span><hr size=1> Epics were kunark era weapons, maybe some of you are just getting to the point of epic, but in a few months it will be 2 years since i've had epic. At some point, it's normal that it becomes outdated. Velious and now luclin didn't bring in new pets for mages, it looks like PoP will... GOOD. <br>
<br>
Everything in EQ scales up, my uber planar equip that was helping me kill vox/nagy is long gone, my HoT armor that helped me break in NToV has also mostly been replaced. It's called progression. That insane pet that is the epic will also (I hope) be replaced one day. Would be a good thing. <br>
<br>
People who complain about epic possibly being overshadowed by better pets, think about this few things.<br>
<br>
1) You don't know the nature of those pets, for all we know they might be only useable in extraplanar zones, wich would leave epic the best thing in 4/5 of the game. They might be weaker than epic (I sure hope not), wich would leave epic the best pet in game (i sure hope not).<br>
<br>
2) Epic might be a requirement for certain quests.<br>
<br>
3) Even if those pets are better than epic, they might drop from Uber_god00 and you might NEVER see those like lots of people have never seen VP/ST/VT, the casual people will never get the same thing the ubers do, at least not in the same time frame. While casual are now slowly breakin in NTOV, the ubers are redoing their equip in VT. <br>
<br>
4) Even though we all pay the same cash to play, we don't all use the same content and without scaled content, the game would have died 3 years ago. No you don't deserve epic/xxx spell or xxx piece of uber loot. You pay to play a game, not to be entitled to something in that game. You want it bad? Join a raiding guild, spend the hours to get to that stage and go kill the big mofo for your dream item, simple as that. You don't deserve x item/spell/epic just for paying the price of the game. You don't deserve to &quot;finish&quot; EQ because you bought the game, you don't deserve to have best pet in game forever because you completed 1 quest. If you found epic to be that hard, chances are you won't see better than epic anytime soon, even if the new pets are better than epic, so it shouldn't really matters to you that those pets are better. Why? Because they will most likely require even more work than epic to get. PoP will be a though expansion. There is going to be lots of hard stuff to kill and mudflation will be bigger than ever. I don't think there will be many thing to do in PoP for non raiding people, because, well, it's an expansion of PLANES. From the looks of it, it will be 18 raiding zone (prolly scaling from a few old plane thoughness place to post VT insane planes of doom) and 2 or so &quot;cities&quot; plane. A spelll being in the spell file doesn't mean YOU are entitled to that spell.<br>
<br>
5) Epic is nearly 2 years old, it needs to be replaced at some point, that's a fact. It may be frustrating for some of you who will complete their epics close to PoP release, but remember a) if you just got your epic, you might be far from seeing the new pets and b) welcome to the world of warriors who, for the most part, completed their epic to realise a few weeks later they were better of with the willsapper or jade mace they ALREADY HAD hehe.<br>
<br>
6) Epics have became much easier as time passed. Mage epic was a serious bitch when it came out because people had to break to 7th island sky with at most kunark gear. Most epic mobs were hard, BY KUNARK STANDARDS. Nowadays most epic mobs are pushovers. People have insane ratio weapons, ntov loot, ssra loot, vt loot, clearing sky is more a matter of time invested than accomplishment now. AAs, equip, levels, experience, bazaar, etc, all adds up to making epics trivials.<br>
<br>
To conclude, my wish is that people would stop whining about epic being &quot;HYPOTHETICALY&quot; replaced in PoP by better pets. It's about damn time if you ask me. Epic will still be the best pet you have until you can achieve the new pets. Epic will still be a security pet that you could pop up for no mana (assuming you have a brain and keep a charged rod on you at all time) in emergency. Epic will most likely still be the best all around pet (sure new earth might have more hp and be &quot;better&quot; in that way, but will it have the damage sheild? sure new water might backstab for 500 and leave epic in the dust DPS wise, but it might be lacking on tanking and HPs, see where I'm going?). Epic will still be a status symbol. Epic will always be epic no matter what. Now please everyone be happy that we will have new advancement potential beyong epic, and SMILE!<br>
<br>
