3) if you can't get friends/guildies to help ya, it is your problem really. My point was it's much much easier to do with people in velious armor, with primals, AAs, res stick, summon robe, etc than when the first people did it 2-3 years ago wearing crafted armor and weilding ykesha. Also note that crown is common drop, you'll usualy get at least 1 (usualy 2-3) per clearing.<br>
<br>
Our epic is one of the hardest/longest/&lt;insert other &quot;est&quot; word here&gt;, but it also is one of the best (not many epic have as much impact as mage epic does) and it had a long life at the top of the pet food chain. MAGES should be the master of pets, not their epic. No other epics will be &quot;scaled&quot; to match with the upcomming expansion, why should mage one be? It's the special magical item that makes you the best mage forever? After you get epic might as well retire then... I almost quit my mage just before luclin came out, felt there was no progression anymore for me (AAs changed that). If 3 expansions later I still don't have better pets to look up too, what you think will happen? =p<br>
<br>
Epic are called epic because of the time involved in questing them (except maybe rogue and shaman ones =p) and the reward is damn good for the level you can get them at. However, they are not &quot;end game&quot;. People in the end game need the old carrot on a stick to keep them playing, they want something to look foward to. I want better pets then epic at level 65. Don't wanna be stuck with same old pet I had for 2 years (+ minor upgrades of the caster balancing, but still same old pet). For those of you that still consider epic &quot;special&quot;, he will always be, the new pets look like they will be earth/fire/air/water like old pets, not a mixed elemental like epic is, so epic will always have it's place in the 46-60 range too.<br>
<br>
